events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Lu Dort scored 24 points, Darius Bazley added 21 points and 10 rebounds, and the Oklahoma City Thunder snapped a 14-game skid with a 119-115 win over the Boston Celtics on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder snap 14-game skid with 119-115 win over Celtics

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 29 points and 12 rebounds, Brook Lopez added 22 points and the Milwaukee Bucks held off the Charlotte Hornets 114-104 on Tuesday night to avoid a sweep of the teams' regular-season series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks avoid series sweep with 114-104 win over Hornets

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 27 points on nine 3-pointers, one shy of Damian Lillard's franchise record, and the Portland Trail Blazers routed the Indiana Pacers 133-112 on Tuesday night to end their five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Portland ends 5-game skid with 3-point flurry at Indiana

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored seven of his 17 points in the fourth quarter, Jeff Green had 22 points and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Toronto Raptors 116-103 Tuesday night and clinched a playoff spot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Nets rally past Raptors 116-103, clinch playoff spot

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored 31 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Houston Rockets 114-107 on Tuesday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves beat Rockets 114-107 for third straight win

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 39 points and the short-handed Dallas Mavericks jumped on Golden State from the start to thump the Warriors 133-103 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 39 points as short-handed Mavs pound Warriors
